# üé® ASCII Art - Images Converter & Web Interface üñºÔ∏è
## Project Overview

This repository contains a project utilizing **Java**, **Spring**, **React**, and **TypeScript** for transforming images into its visual representation using ASCII characters (ASCII Art). [See an Example](#example-images-of-converting-donkey-image-into-its-visual-representation-using-ascii-characters-ascii-art)




### Client-Side (React/TypeScript) üåê 

- **User Interface:** Web-based interface created using React and TypeScript for:
    - üñºÔ∏è **Image Upload & Processing:** Upload images for conversion into ASCII characters representaion.
    - üé® **Customization Options:** Customize resolution and character set to generate varied ASCII outputs.
    - üì• **Output:** Obtain ASCII representation of uploaded images in downloadable HTML format.
    - üåÄ **Process Overview:** Additionally, a brief explanation of the process along with examples of ASCII images is provided in the interface.
- **Technologies & Usage**
    - Utilizes **React**, **TypeScript**, and Ant Design UI library for a dynamic interface.
    - Functional React components with hooks and **Axios** for handle async requests.




[Screenshots of the client side](#web-interface)

### Server-Side (Java/Spring)  üñ•Ô∏è

- **Image to ASCII Converter:** **Java** program converting images into ASCII representations, allowing resolution adjustments and character set modifications.

- **Spring-based Java Server:** Utilizes Spring framework, featuring endpoints for:
    - üì• Returning an image its maximum ASCII Art resolution.
    - üñºÔ∏è Given an image, generating its ASCII representation based on specific character sets and resolution.



## How to Use

### Server Setup üèóÔ∏è

1. üåê Clone the repository and navigate to the server directory.
2. üöÄ Run the Spring server application.

### Client Interface üñ•Ô∏è

1. üõ†Ô∏è Install necessary npm dependencies (`package.json`).
2. üöÄ Start the React application.

## Running the Project üèÉ‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è

### Server üñ•Ô∏è

- Ensure Java and Spring environments are set up.
- Define `UPLOAD_DIRECTORY` for file storage.

### Client üåê

- Configure Node.js and npm for React and TypeScript.
- Utilize the React app for image uploads and ASCII downloads.

## Server - Usage üé®

### File Upload Endpoint üì§

- **Route:** `POST /upload`
- **Description:** Uploads an image file, returning its maximum ASCII resolution.
- **Parameters:** `image` (MultipartFile)
- **Returns:** `ResponseEntity<Integer>`

### ASCII Image Retrieval Endpoint üñºÔ∏è

- **Route:** `GET /download/{chars}/{res}`
- **Description:** Retrieves ASCII art of the uploaded image, based on provided characters and resolution.
- **Parameters:** `{chars}` (String), `{res}` (int)
- **Returns:** `ResponseEntity<Resource>`
